items.text: 527 Fried Carrot Cake #01-117. Tasty black carrot cake and good chilli.
Song Kee Fish Ball Noodle #1-123
Love the fishball here
Try #01-126 the porridge is nice!
#01-126 Ann Hoo Cooked Food offers value for money and yummy zhap chai png!
Lunch Time :)
Chicken rice. The serving from Zhou Kee #01-146 was uneventful for me
Wantan noodles. 2 options: A) Hup Heng 01-141 & B) Capitol 01-140. (A) is slightly better: substantial wantans (with chopped water chestnuts) & thick char siew (BBQ pork). Char siew from (B) was hard
Having breakfast
Cheap and good vegetarian stall at #01-143.
Try 01-132 carrot cake!!!! Been here since I young!!!!
Soon kueh at Hwa Huat is good. But face of the lady boss is super black!!
Lee Heng cooked food stall serves nice and huge varieties of veggies and meat. Serves porridge and rice as well.
Most of the coffee stall are expert for their coffee. Price here is good. You will be happy. Big cup SGD0.80/cup coffee with milk.
Must try the ice kachang at 春宝 stall #01-136. Nice
chendol is gd at 春宝
yongtaufoo facing carpark is simple, no-bs comfort food. awesome.
try the nasi lemak at 01-105 the chicken is superb
Nice vegetarian stall!
ying yi kway chap: it's above average, but falls short of stellar. i like their preserved vegetables and big intestines.
Poh hua coffee drinks stall #01-118 not even serve tasty coffee!! Their bread can be lagi soft or even crispy, definitely best with their beautiful half-boiled eggs! Friendly uncle and auntie!!
Tasty chai tow kway from Chun Cheng #01-113. Evenly fried, and fried eggs bind the top & bottom, like Chey Sua in Toa Payoh
Stall 8 - carrot cake is the best!
01-130 香记粿条面汤 is good... Like their dry noodle with chili... Noodle not too dry nor too soggy, it's jus nice... Chili is superb. 01-128 Everyday Tea stall: whether Tea and Coffee both r equally gd!
Great duck drumstick noodles and big wanton soup at #01-140!
The chicken rice is nice:)
Try the ice kachang store at #01-36, order corn milk or longan milk nice
Ah Tee Coffee Drinks Stall, #01-107 their Kopi-O is good but some may find other stall better. Depends on individual taste.
Fu Mun Chicken Rice #01-110 is yummy
Try the chicken rice behind the Malay stalls.
new vegetarian store wif brown rice open few mths ago..
Hiap Lee wonton noodle is great for breakfast! The char siew is roasted just nice...
Vegetarian food..gd
2nd cup of kopi at Everyday Tea Store need not Q. The store owner can recognize U after yr 1st purchase . Awesome!
Capitol roasted rice.noodles not bad! #01-140
Stall 01-115 Hai Kee Cooked Food. Nice Fried Carrot Cake.
Nice cooked food stall n cheap @ #01-126.  Try the fish cake n their fresh cooked fish.
The lady in "house of sugarcane" is super rude. I rather buy the sugarcane drink from the fruit stall aunty, cheaper, sweeter and the service is million times better.
Good teochew kuay teow mee.
...go vegetarian...
Try the Ann hoo cooked food.. V nice
Song kee fishball noodle. Ever since they change the min price to $4, the queue is killed by more than 70%. It's a cruel world. Meanwhile the chicken noodle beside set min to $3 a bowl (was $2.5)
The Best Fried Carrot Cake, white only is @ stall Hai Kee Cooked Food #01-115. Close on every Mon n usually by noon time the carrot cake will be finished.
Good food.
Shredded chicken + wantans. Chye Kee #01-122 serves this interesting combo, together with braised mushroom slices. The wantans stood out: generous, juicy minced meat fillings
Tracy's sarawak kitchen nice
#01-117 fried carrot cake is nice. Their kueh kueh also not bad. 3 for $1
满福chicken rice very good! Boneless wings(white) beautifully cut.
everyday tea stall: coffee is good! they don't serve them in regular sizes however - you can only choose between small or large cups.
Lontong is the best.
Ba Zhang at He Le very nice but    run out quickly
Must try the 海南咖哩剪刀剪 at #01-119.
Curry Rice stall at middle row used to be good. Now they gives miserable servings. Totally not value for money.
😜Good economic food market stall.✌
Love the fried hokkien prawn mee. Simple tasty
The veg kway chap here is the best.
botak noodle
San yuan service is from good to worst now..I think they hire wrong uncle to serve customer in a polite way..omfg..-.-"
I like the lor mee here
One of the very famous and nice hainanese chicken rice stall around the area. (stall 01-146, facing the carpark)
Nice lor lee~
Try de kway chap here is nice
Everyday Tea Stall #01-128 A popular drinks store👍
Try the curry rice store at #01-119. cheap and good!
Black carrot cake!
EVERYDAY TEA STALL (Stall 01-128) have very nice coffee!!
Love the Kway Chap.
nice wanton mee, wif chestnut inside wanton..
Porridge and chicken rice good.
The chicken rice, kuey chap, and carrot cake.. All yummilicious.
The chicken rice in 福满 is nice if you mind the long queue of the hainanese chicken Rick at #01-146 facing the carpark. Can give it a try.
Fishball noodles. Tasty handmade Fishball from Song Kee #01-123. Bouncy/chewy, not too salty. Comes with 'her giao' (fish dumpling), which many stalls no longer serve today
#01-124 Wanton Mee
the teo chew porridge is fabulous..
Nice cooked vegetarian stall 01-143.
Kuay chap here is the best!! ^^
Kuey zhup stall directly BEHIND #01-146 is tasty. Can try.
Gik Gik Heng #01-129 served herbal prawn/pork ribs mee and lor mee. Love the herbal taste of the broth and lor mee might looks very thick but actually it's not. Worth a try
You must try the vegetarian food here... Delicious!!
Very local kind of hawker center with an amazing amount of traditional breakfast options. Had a great lontong, as well as carrot cake.
